{"title":"OneUp MTB Hubs Debut w/ Colorful, Affordable Design","link":"https://bikerumor.com/oneup-components-mountain-bike-hubs/","date":1719456094000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-8-1536x1025.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" alt=\"oneup mtb hubs on a bike.\" /></p>\n<p>OneUp Components wanted a lightweight hub, an affordable hub, and a quality, reliable hub. Usually, you can pick two, but they’re delivering all three, and they come in seven colors.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1354\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-1.jpg\" alt=\"oneup mtb hubs on a bike.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-1.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-1-297x201.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-1-1536x1040.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-1-120x81.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-1-768x520.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The CNC’d alloy hub shells pack simple but proven tech inside, are rated for any type of bike, from XC to long-travel eMTBs. Here’s how they come together…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"799\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-6.jpg\" alt=\"disassembled parts of oneup mtb hubs.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-6.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-6-297x119.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-6-1536x614.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-6-120x48.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-6-768x307.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The hub shell is machined from 7075 alloy, and it’s easily user-serviceable with a mostly tool-free disassembly, save for bearings…you’ll need a press to replace those and pull the axle out (<em>properly</em>, anyway).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4.jpg\" alt=\"internal view of oneup mtb hub shell.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-4-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The inner drive ring nested into CNC’d grooves rather than being threaded in. They say this saves weight, allows wider bearing spacing, and makes it simpler to assemble and maintain.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1713\" height=\"1141\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5.jpg\" alt=\"internal cutaway view of oneup mtb hubs.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5.jpg 1713w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5-1536x1023.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-5-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Claimed weight is just 362g for the pair – 142g front and 220g rear (w/ XD freehub). This is lighter than most competing mainstream hubs on the market, at about half the price.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key specs include:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>44-tooth ratchet ring</li>\n\n\n\n<li>8.2º engagement</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Enduro ABEC 5 Bearings</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Double-seal endcaps</li>\n\n\n\n<li>7 colors</li>\n\n\n\n<li>J-Bend spokes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>6-bolt rotor mount</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Boost spacing (110 F / 148 R)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>28 and 32 hole</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2.jpg\" alt=\"oneup mtb hubs shown in purple.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The endcap’s seals have waterproof grease applied between them and the bearing’s seals, and each hubset comes with a packet of DumondeTech waterproof grease for topping it off.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-9-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Repairs should be easy, too. They use common J-Bend spokes, and the build specs are laser etched onto the hub shell for easy reference.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7.jpg\" alt=\"freehub body options for oneup mtb hubs.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-7-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They’re available with HG, XD/XD-R, and Micro Spline freehub bodies…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"782\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-3.jpg\" alt=\"oneup mtb hubs shown in all colors.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-3.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-3-297x116.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-3-1536x601.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-3-120x47.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oneup-mountain-bike-hubs-3-768x300.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>…in your choice of Black, Pewter, Green, Orange, Red, Purple, and Blue. MSRP is just $370 for the set, or $100 for the front and $220 for the rear plus $50 for your choice of FH body.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.oneupcomponents.com/collections/hubs\" target=\"_blank\">OneUpComponents.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/oneup-components-mountain-bike-hubs/\">OneUp MTB Hubs Debut w/ Colorful, Affordable Design</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b1f0c9c2b3ead28643ff891a6bea3e4e8ad92582b6a5180ef9657883926c430f","category":"Cycling"}